Edith Johnson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edith_Johnson 0 Edith Johnson (August 10, 1894 – September 6, 1969) was an American actress of the silent era. She appeared in 66 films between 1913 and 1924. She was born in Rochester, New York and died in Los Angeles, California.
